My anxious attachment has pretty much like looked this since I started dating my boyfriend…(this song by @kellyclarkson has always encompassed exactly how I felt in my relationships)…
〰️
It’s been quite a learning curve since I’ve never really been in a healthy relationship with a stable and kind man…
〰️
But no matter who I am with, my anxious attachment never fails to show up!
〰️
I have done so much hard work on becoming more secure in my current relationship and more trusting of it, which has not been easy…
〰️
So what has helped me through this process?
✅ Open communication with my partner
✅ Taking things SLOW
✅ Patience
✅ Learning about co-dependency and attachment theory
✅ Making sure I have my own life outside of the relationship!
〰️
Can you relate to any of these? Share you expedite with anxious attachment in the comments! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
〰️

Have you ever heard of healing anxiety with a “savoring walk?”
〰️
This is one of my favorite ways to get out of my head and into the present moment…
〰️
Whenever I begin to ruminate with anxious thoughts, I get up and go outside for a walk. It’s can be for 5 minutes or 5 hours, but it never fails to break me out of those loud negative thoughts patterns.
〰️
If you are reading this and feeling anxious, get up and go outside…take a walk if you can. If not, just breath in the fresh air and pay attention to all of the sights and sounds around you. What do you see? What do you hear?
〰️
You are safe right in this moment…
〰️
Tag someone you would go on a savoring walk with and leave a comment on where you would love to take a savoring walk ⬇️⬇️⬇️
〰️

I can’t believe how much I can relate too all of these…
〰️
Sometimes my anxiety makes it just too overwhelming for me to stick with I have planned…
〰️
Many times it’s because I’m too exhausted to face the world and pretend that I’m ok…
〰️
Other times it’s because I don’t want to be a burden and I really need to be alone…
〰️
All I know is that when I cancel plans it’s not because I didn’t want to follow through, but it’s because my anxiety is screaming at me that danger is around the corner and I don’t know how to fight it..
〰️
Nowadays, I make plans based on what I want to do and not what others expect of me. I’m a recovering people pleaser so I’m learning how to say NO more often without feeling bad about it. And I’m learning how to set boundaries with myself and others.
〰️
I make plans, but I give myself grace and compassion if I wake up one morning and feel too overwhelmed to follow through.
〰️
The people in your life who support you and love you will understand and not judge you.
〰️
